{"title_page": "Montserrat/Military", "text_new": "#REDIRECT [[Montserrat]]\n\n{{R from subpage}}\n", "text_old": "#REDIRECT [[Montserrat]]\n", "name_user": "1234qwer1234qwer4", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:R from subpage", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Montserrat/Military&redirect=no"}
{"title_page": "Clark Saturn", "text_new": "'''Clark Saturn''', also known as '''Clark ov Saturn''', is an American musician, DJ, actor, filmmaker, comedian, and executive of the [[New Kingston Film Festival]] in [[New Kingston, New York]]. As an actor, Saturn was principal in many national and international commercials between 1999 and 2006.<ref>{{cite web\n | last = Freeman Gill\n | first = John\n | title = Weatherperson Wanted. Bring Own Map. And Jokes \n | date = 2005-05-22\n | website = New York Times\n | url = https://www.nytimes.com/2005/05/22/nyregion/thecity/22weat.html\n | accessdate = 2009-04-22 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web\n | last = Westword\n | first = Denver\n | title = Best of Denver 2001: Best Career Upgrade by a Former Local\n | date = 2001-03-29\n | website = Denver Westword\n | url = http://www.westword.com/2001-03-29/calendar/best-career-upgrade-by-a-former-local\n | accessdate = 2009-04-22 }}</ref> He also acted in several student films and self-produced films with friends Heidi Sjursen (A Potato Chip Tale) <ref>{{cite web\n | last = Database\n | first = Internet Movie\n | title = A Potato Chip Tale: 2004 \n | date = 2005-05-22\n | website = Internet Movie Database\n | url = https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0455694/\n | accessdate = 2009-04-22 }}</ref> and Andrew Hubschmann (American Walker).\n\nAs a music producer and performer, Saturn is best known for his work with electronic duos Socks and Sandals (with Nicolas Sauser) and pH10 (with Recone F. Helmut),<ref>{{cite web\n | last = Lemieux\n | first = Kelly\n | title = Chemistry Class \n | date = 1997-12-18\n | website = Denver Westword\n | url = http://www.westword.com/1997-12-18/music/chemistry-class\n | accessdate = 2009-04-22 }}</ref> and LD-50.<ref>{{cite web\n | last = Mayo\n | first = James\n | title = Lethal Dose: LD-50 makes electronic music that doesn't go down smooth \n | date = 1997-03-13\n | website = Denver Westword\n | url = http://www.westword.com/1997-03-13/music/lethal-dose\n | accessdate = 2009-04-22 }}</ref> Saturn was a resident DJ in Brooklyn, NY at Halcyon's Sunday evening \"Undercity\" party, along with DJs Spinoza, Sheldon Drake, Mercy_Killah, HazMaat and others. In the realm of new media, Saturn was at the forefront of the videoblog revolution of the mid-2000s, and created the popular videoblogs ZipZapZop.com and MyGermanClass.com, which won a Best of 2006 People's Choice award for video podcasts from Apple's iTunes. Saturn's video interview of Todd Polenburg called \"Bush Bush Revolution\" was featured on Rocketboom.<ref>{{cite web\n | last = .com\n | first = Rocketboom\n | title = Thursday, August 25, 2005: Special Feature \n | date = 2005-08-25\n | website = Rocketboom.com\n | url = http://www.rocketboom.com/rb_05_aug_25/\n | accessdate = 2009-04-22 }}</ref>\n\n==Biography==\nClark ov Saturn was born in [[Cedar Falls, Iowa|Cedar Falls]], [[Iowa]] as \"Baby Boy Wood\" on June 26, 1969, and was soon thereafter adopted and named Clark Jason Nelson. He graduated from Aurelia High School a year early and attended school at Bryne Videregaaende Skule in Bryne, Norway. He received a B.A. in German with a minor in Scandinavian Studies from [[Luther College (Iowa)|Luther College]] in Decorah, Iowa in 1991. During the mid-1990s, he became well known in Denver, Colorado as \"Herr Nelson\" who taught high school German for the Denver Public Schools on their [[Public-access television]] [[cable TV]] channel in a show called \"Tele Deutsch\".<ref>{{cite web\n | last = Perez-Giese\n | first = Tony\n | title = Sprechen Sie Interactive? The revolution may not be televised; the German class will be \n | date = 1996-12-19\n | website = Denver Westword\n | url = http://www.westword.com/1996-12-19/news/sprechen-sie-interactive\n | accessdate = 2009-04-22 }}</ref> The stage name \"Clark ov Saturn\" began being used in 1994 for various musical projects. After joining the industrial band LD-50, Saturn and Recone Helmut split off and formed pH10 and moved to New York City in 1999 after touring Europe with Dr. Israel and the Trumystic Sound System. While in New York, Saturn pursued acting, music production, DJing, filmmaking, standup comedy, improvisation, and online education. In 2005, Saturn started a videoblog, ZipZapZop.com as well as MyGermanClass.com.\n\n==Trivia==\nClark ov Saturn is left-handed.\nClark had a son, Rishi, born on April 3, 2007. A Socks and Sandals EP on Microcosm Music was named for him, Rishi Saturn.\n\n==References==\n{{refbegin}}\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{refend}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.clarksaturn.com] - Clark ov Saturn's homepage.\n*{{IMDb name|1886637}}\n*[http://spacetruckingmogul.com/socksandsandals/] Socks and Sandals homepage\n*[http://microcosm-music.com/socksandsandals.html] Socks and Sandals on Microcosm-Music\n*[http://mygermanclass.com] MyGermanClass.com\n*[http://zipzapzop.com] ZipZapZop.com\n\n==Articles==\n*[http://spacetruckingmogul.com/articles/aurelia.html] Aurelia Star newspaper article\n*[http://www.westword.com/1996-12-19/news/sprechen-sie-interactive] Denver Westword Article\n*''New York Times'': [https://www.nytimes.com/2005/05/22/nyregion/thecity/22weat.html \"Weatherperson Wanted. Bring Own Map. And Jokes. \"]\n*''Denver Westword'': [http://www.westword.com/2001-03-29/calendar/best-career-upgrade-by-a-former-local] \"Best Career Upgrade by a Former Local\"\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Saturn, Clark}}\n[[Category:American filmmakers]]\n[[Category:21st-century American comedians]]\n[[Category:People from Cedar Falls, Iowa]]\n[[Category:American electronic musicians]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American male television actors]]\n[[Category:American DJs]]\n[[Category:1969 births]]\n[[Category:Luther College (Iowa) alumni]]\n[[Category:Electronic dance music DJs]]\n", "text_old": "'''Clark Saturn''', also known as '''Clark ov Saturn''', is an American musician, DJ, actor, filmmaker, comedian, and executive of the [[New Kingston Film Festival]] in 